    "linkedinUrl": "https://www.linkedin.com/posts/ian-leslie-mba-5ab30513b_im-excited-to-share-that-i-recently-started-activity-7474838448487542785-8Bo1",
    "content": "I’m excited to share that I recently started in my new role as Regional Public Affairs Manager at Flock . I’m grateful to be part of work that sits at the intersection of community, public policy, and technology. At Flock, we believe safety is a fundamental right, and we build public safety technology designed to help communities, businesses, and law enforcement reduce and solve crime. \n\nBut technology alone is never enough. Lasting success requires community education, meaningful public input, and local control over how these tools are adopted and used. It also requires thoughtful advocacy for the right guardrails so that safety, trust, accountability, and transparency move forward together. I’m proud to be part of that work and of the broader conversation around helping communities engage with new public safety technology in an informed and responsible way. \n\nI’m also grateful to Trevor L. Chandler , Kam Simmons , Holly Beilin , and Joshua Thomas  for the opportunity and support along the way.",
